      <hedline>
        <hl1>ING TO ACQUIRE RELIASTAR</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Andrew Ross Sorkin</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Sorkin, Andrew Ross</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Dutch bank ING Group NV acquires Minneapolis-based life insurer ReliaStar for $54 a share, total of $5.1 billion; will also assume about $1 billion in debt; ING chairman Godfried van der Lugt comments; photo (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The Dutch bank ING Group N.V. reached an agreement to acquire the Minneapolis-based life insurer ReliaStar for $54 a share, a total of $5.1 billion. It will also assume about $1 billion in debt. The move is part of ING's ambition of ''substantially increasing our presence in the U.S. and furthering our position as a financial services leader in North America,'' its chairman, Godfried van der Lugt, said.</p>
        <p>Andrew Ross Sorkin</p>
      </block>
